<br>
I heard that you still med while casting if you're on a horse so I was wondering if it'd be worth the 8.5k to buy a horse to summon just when I MS.<br>
<br>
Also I know there was a formula to figure out how much mana you med based on your meditation skill but can't seem to find it anywhere now... would anyone happen to know how it works? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utatankawd.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tatankawd</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/10/02 4:22:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26272.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: MSing and horses</span><hr size=1> Meditation formula:<br>
<br>
Med skill/12 = mana regen/tick sitting<br>
+1 mana/tick regen while standing<br>
<br>
At top med skill (252), a char regens 21 mana/tick while medding.<br>
<br>
There is a different formula posted on Graffe's, in the Library section, that I can state unequivocally is wrong.<br>
<br>
------<br>
<br>
What are manastones going for these days?  Last night a guy in bazaar channel was selling one for 22kpp, didn't know if that was good or not (didn't buy it, didn't have the cash).<br>
<br>
After he auctioned it, a newb asked what a manastone was.  Lots of us got a good chuckle from that =)<br>
